# Clone the redding-stan repo.
# Big! Takes a while, by far the longest step.

git clone https://github.com/dmuck/redding-stan --recursive redding-stan

cd redding-stan

# Uncomment the line CXX=clang++ if so desired in makefile

make check

# If prompted: make install

bin/stanc --version

make examples/bernoulli/bernoulli

# Start redding-stan:

rob@Rob-M1 redding-stan % ./examples/bernoulli/bernoulli   

ReddingStan version 1.0

ReddingStan is free software and comes with ABSOLUTELY NO WARRANTY.

Type 'help' for some help, 'list' a list of commands.

[redding]$ load examples/bernoulli/bernoulli.data.R
[INFO] model initialized with data from "examples/bernoulli/bernoulli.data.R"

[redding]$ eval_J_true 0.2
-8.97767
-3.59801
48
""
[redding]$ eval_J_true 0.3
-9.35226
-3.89331
18
""
[redding]$ quit
